mer Militants of Banned Outfit Among Those on Election Duty in Darjeeling |url=https://www.news18.com/news/politics/former-militants-of-banned-outfit-among-those-on-election-duty-in-darjeeling-2105749.html |website=News18 |accessdate=15 October 2019|quote=The organisation, banned by the Union government in 2014, aims to carve out a separate Kamtapur nation from India, {{sic|comprising |hide=y|of}} six districts in West Bengal and four in Assam}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=BASUMATARY |first1=RINOY |title=KLO vows to launch armed liberation struggle against 'India' |url=https://nenow.in/north-east-news/klo-vows-to-launch-armed-liberation-struggle-against-india.html |website=NORTHEAST NOW |accessdate=15 October 2019|quote=That imperialist India is the main enemy of our national struggle. Independent Kamatapur shall comprise the entire Kamatapur in India.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Selvaraj6 |first1=A |title=Suspected member of Kamtapur militant group arrested in Chennai {{!}} Chennai News - Times of India |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/suspected-member-of-kamtapur-militant-group-arrested-in-chennai/articleshow/69055883.cms |website=The Times of India |accessdate=15 October 2019 |language=en|quote=The Chennai city police on Friday arrested a suspected member of an extremist organization that demands carving out a separate state - Kamtapur - from West Bengal and Assam.}}</ref>\n* Proposed state: [[Kamtapur]]\n** Ethnic group: [[Rajbongshi people|Kamtapuri]]\n** Militant organization: [[File:Flag of the Kamtapur Liberation Organisation.png|22px|border]] [[Kamtapur Liberation Organisation]]\n\n[[Karbi Anglong district|Karbistan]]\n* Proposed state: [[Karbi Anglong district|Karbi]]\n** Ethnic group: [[Karbi people|Karbi]]\n** Militant organization: [[File:Flag of Karbi Longri N.C. Hills Liberation Front.svg|border|22px]] [[Karbi Longri N.C. Hills Liberation Front]]\n\n[[Manipur]]\n* Proposed state: [[Manipur]]\n** Ethnic group: [[Meitei people|Meitei]]\n** Militant organization: [[File:Bandera UNLF.svg|22px|border]] [[United National Liberation Front|UNLF]], [[File:Bandera FPRM Manipur.png|22px|border]] [[People's Liberation Army of Manipur|PLA]], [[File:South Asian Communist Banner.svg|22px|border]] [[Kangleipak Communist Party]], [[People's Revolutionary Party of Kangleipak]], [[Kanglei Yawol Kanna Lup]], [[File:South Asian Communist Banner.svg|22px|border]] [[Maoist Communist Party of Manipur]]\n\n[[Nagaland]]\n* Proposed state: [[Nagalim]]\n{{main|Naga nationalism}}\n** Ethnic group: [[Naga people|Naga]], [[Pnar people|Pnars]]\n** Militant organization: [[File:Unofficial flag of Nagaland.svg|22px|border]] [[NSCN]]\n\n[[Punjab]]\n* Proposed state: [[Khalistan]] \n** Ethnic-Religious group: [[Punjabi Sikh]]\n\n[[Tamil Nadu]]\n{{main|Tamil nationalism}}\n* Proposed state: [[File:Tamil Nationalist flag.jpg|22px]] [[File:Tamil Nationalist flag variant .jpg|22px]] [[Tamilakam]], [[Dravida Nadu]]\n** Ethnic group: [[Tamils]]\n** Militant organization: [[Tamil nationalism|Tamil separatists]]\n*** Advocacy groups and Pressure groups: [[Tamil National Alliance]], [[Tamil Nadu Liberation Army]], [[Tamil United National Front]], [[Tamil National Retrieval Troops]], [[Tamil Thesa Pothuvudaimai Katchi]], [[Upsurging People Force]], [[Tamil Self-Determination People Front]], [[Tamil Elders Council]], [[World Tamil Movement]]\n \n[[Tripura]]\n{{main|Tripuri nationalism}}\n* Proposed state: [[Tripura]]\n** Ethnic group: [[Tripuri people|Tripuri]]\n** Militant organizations: [[File:Flag of the National Liberation Front of Tripura.png|22px|border]] [[NLFT]], [[All Tripura Tiger Force]]\n** Political parties: [[Indigenous Nationalist Party of Twipra]], [[Indigenous People's Front of Tripura]], [[National Socialist Party of Tripura]], [[Tripura Hill People's Party]]\n\n== Indonesia ==\n{{Main|Seccession in Indonesia}}\n{{See also|List of active separatist movements in Oceania#Indonesia}}\n\n[[File:Flag of Aceh.png|22px|border]] [[Aceh]]\n*Ethnic groups: [[Acehnese people|Acehnese]]\n**Proposed state: [[File:Flag of Free Aceh Movement.svg|22x20px|border]] [[Aceh|Republic of Aceh]]\n**Militant organisation: [[Free Aceh Movement]] (negotiated peace with the Indonesian government in 2005, and now it is a civil movement, but the separatism still has supporters)\n\n[[File:Flag of Bali.svg|22px|border]] [[Bali]]\n*Ethnic group: [[Balinese people|Balinese]] \n**Proposed state:[[Bali|Balinese Republic]]<ref>http://www.muslimedianews.com/2014/08/tahun-2015-indonesia-pecah-ini-petanya.html</ref><ref>https://www.facebook.com/Gerakan-Bali-Merdeka-173532122764277/</ref>\n**Advocacy group: [[Baduy Society]], [[Bali Fourm]], [[Bali Freedom Movement]]\n**Political party: [[Dharma Awakening Party]]\n\n[[File:Flag of North Sumatra.svg|22px|border]] [[North Sumatra|Batakia]]\n*Ethnic group: [[Bataks]]\n**Proposed state:[[North Sumatra|Batakia]]<ref>http://parlinpakpahan.blogspot.com.es/2010/03/lmmt-solusi-politik-untuk-pemekaran.html</ref>\n**Political party: [[Batak Nation Party]]\n**Advocacy group: [[Bangso Batak]], [[O Tano Batak]], [[Batak Heritage Society]], [[Batak Worldwide]], [[Arys Christian Sinambela]], [[Batak Nauli]], [[Free Batak Homeland]], [[Free North Sumatra]]\n\n[[Kalimantan]]\n* Proposed state: [[File:Flag of Kalimantan Borneo.png|22x20px|border]] [[Kalimantan Borneo]], unification with {{flag|Malaysia}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tribunnews.com/nasional/2011/08/04/perhatian-buruk-warga-perbatasan-ancam-kibarkan-bendera-malaysia |title=Perhatian Buruk! Warga Perbatasan Ancam Kibarkan Bendera Malaysia |publisher=Tribun News |date=4 August 2011 |accessdate=4 July 2014 |language=Indonesian |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714152715/http://www.tribunnews.com/nasional/2011/08/04/perhatian-buruk-warga-perbatasan-ancam-kibarkan-bendera-malaysia |archive-date=14 July 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.itoday.co.id/politik/duh-wni-di-perbatasan-ancam-gabung-ke-malaysia?q=/politik/7351-duh-wni-di-perbatasan-ancam-gabung-ke-malaysia |title=Duh, WNI di Perbatasan Ancam Gabung ke Malaysia |publisher=I Today |date=1 May 2012 |accessdate=4 July 2014 |language=Indonesian |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714151218/http://www.itoday.co.id/politik/duh-wni-di-perbatasan-ancam-gabung-ke-malaysia?q=%2Fpolitik%2F7351-duh-wni-di-perbatasan-ancam-gabung-ke-malaysia |archive-date=14 July 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jpnn.com/index.php?mib=berita.detail&id=91667 |title=Sejumlah Kecamatan Perbatasan Ingin Gabung Malaysia |publisher=JPNN |date=11 May 2011 |accessdate=4 July 2014 |language=Indonesian |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140715003308/http://www.jpnn.com/index.php?mib=berita.detail&id=91667 |archive-date=15 July 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jawaban.com/index.php/news/detail/id/91/news/110512133720/limit/0/Warga-Sebatik-Ingin-Gabung-ke-Malaysia-NKRI-Diambang-Kehancuran |title=Warga Sebatik Ingin Gabung ke Malaysia, NKRI Diambang Kehancuran? |publisher=Jawaban News |date=12 May 2011 |accessdate=4 July 2014 |language=Indonesian |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714122303/http://www.jawaban.com/index.php/news/detail/id/91/news/110512133720/limit/0/Warga-Sebatik-Ingin-Gabung-ke-Malaysia-NKRI-Diambang-Kehancuran |archive-date=14 July 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Sulawesi]]\n*Proposed state: [[File:Flag of Sulawesi.svg|22x20px|border]] [[Sulawesi]]\n**Advocacy group: [[Independent Revolutionary Movement of Sulawesi]]\n\n[[File:Flag of North Sulawesi.svg|22px|border]] [[North Sulawesi|Minahasa]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indonesiamatters.com/758/minahasa-nationalism/ |title=Minahasa Nationalism |work=Indonesia Matters |accessdate=23 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nasty-bali.org/sulawesi-separatists.html |title=Christian Sulawesi (Minahasa) seeks independence from Muslim Indonesia |accessdate=23 October 