distan Independence Movement]], [[Kurdistan Democratic Party of Iraq]], [[Patriotic Union of Kurdistan]] (members of the [[Unrepresented Nations and Peoples Organization]])\n** ''De facto'' autonomous state: [[Iraqi Kurdistan]]\n\n{{flag|Assyria}} {{Main|Assyrian nationalism|Assyrian struggle for independence}}\n* Ethnoreligious group: [[Assyrian people|Assyrian]]\n** Proposed state: {{flag|Assyria|name=Assyrian Democratic Republic}}\n** Political parties: [[Assyrian Democratic Movement]], [[Assyria Liberation Party]]\n** Militant organisations: [[Nineveh Plain Protection Units]], [[Dwekh Nawsha]]\n** Advocacy groups: [[Assyrian General Conference]], [[Assyria Council of Europe]]\n\n[[File:Flag of Iraq Turkmen Front.svg|22px|border]] [[Turkmeneli]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Iraqi Turkmen|Turkmen]]\n** Proposed state: [[Turkmeneli]] [[File:Flag of Iraq Turkmen Front.svg|22px|border]] or unification with [[Turkey]]\n** Political party: [[Iraqi Turkmen Front]] (member of the [[Unrepresented Nations and Peoples Organization]])\n\n[[Sinjar Mountain|Sinjar]] {{citation needed|date=July 2017}}\n* Ethnoreligious group: [[Yazidi]]\n** Proposed autonomous area: [[Sinjar]] with [[Sinjar Mountain]] region in {{flag|Iraq}} or unification with {{flag|Kurdistan}}\n** Political organisation: [[Yazidi Movement for Reform and Progress]], [[Yazidis]] Community\n\n== Japan ==\n{{Main|Secession in Japan}}\n\n[[File:Flag of Hokkaido Prefecture.svg|22px|border]] [[Hokkaido]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fourwinds10.net/siterun_data/peace_freedom/patriots_and_protesters/news.php?q=1239483589 |title=FULFORD: An Independent Movement Has Started in Japan's Northern Island of Hokkaido >> Four Winds 10 \u2013 Truth Winds |first=Chris |last=Donahue |website=fourwinds10.net |access-date=12 May 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502031842/http://www.fourwinds10.net/siterun_data/peace_freedom/patriots_and_protesters/news.php?q=1239483589 |archive-date=2 May 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>