omy |title=Yemen's Beleaguered Al Mahrah Seeks Autonomy |access-date=14 July 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150714234058/http://www.geocurrents.info/geopolitics/autonomous-zones/yemens-beleaguered-al-mahrah-seeks-autonomy |archive-date=14 July 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.merip.org/mer/mer263/revolution-socotra |title=Revolution in Socotra \u2013 Middle East Research and Information Project |website=merip.org |access-date=12 February 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150212180956/http://www.merip.org/mer/mer263/revolution-socotra |archive-date=12 February 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.yementimes.com/en/1716/intreview/2950/%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s-a-political-sham-to-set-geographical-regions-based-on-vague-standards-without-any-legal-constitutional-or-political-authority%E2%80%9D.htm |title=Yemen Times [ Offline ] |website=yementimes.com |access-date=12 February 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150212173836/http://www.yementimes.com/en/1716/intreview/2950/%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s-a-political-sham-to-set-geographical-regions-based-on-vague-standards-without-any-legal-constitutional-or-political-authority%E2%80%9D.htm |archive-date=12 February 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n** De facto state: Hadhramaut Region, [[Protectorate of South Arabia]]\n*** Political party: [[File:Hadhrami League Flag.svg|22px|border]] [[Hadhrami League]]\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Lists of active separatist movements]]\n* [[List of historical separatist movements]]\n* [[Autonomous area]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Separatist movements per continent}}\n{{Secession in Countries}}\n{{Irredentism}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Active Separatist Movements in Asia, List Of}}\n[[Category:Asia-related lists|Separatist Movements, Active]]\n[[Category:Disputed territories in Asia|*Separatist Movements in Asia, Active]]\n[[Category:Lists of active separatist movements|Asia]]\n[[Category:Society-related lists|Separatist Movements in Asia, Active]]\n[[Category:Secessionist organizations in Asia| ]]\n[[Category:Myanmar-related lists]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{More citations needed|date=March 2019}}\nThis is a '''list of currently active [[Separatism|separatist]] movements in [[Asia]]'''. Separatism includes [[autonomism]] and [[secession]]ism. What is and is not considered an autonomist or secessionist movement is sometimes contentious. Entries on this list must meet three criteria:\n# They are active movements with current, active members.\n# They are seeking greater autonomy or self-determination for a geographic region (as opposed to personal autonomy).\n# They are the citizens/people of the conflicted area and doesn't come from other countries.\n\nUnder each region listed is one or more of the following:\n* ''De facto'' state: for regions with a ''[[de facto]]'' [[polity]]\n* Proposed state: proposed name for a seceding or anticipated [[sovereign state]]\n* Proposed autonomous area: for movements toward greater [[Autonomous area|autonomy for an area]] but not outright secession\n** ''De facto'' autonomous government: for governments with ''de facto'' autonomous control over a region\n** Government-in-exile: for a [[Government in exile|government based outside of the region in question]], with or without control\n** Political party (or parties): for [[Political party|political parties]] involved in a political system to push for autonomy or secession\n** Militant organisation(s): for [[irregular military|armed organisations]] or [[insurgency|insurgencies]]\n** Advocacy group(s): for [[Advocacy group|nonviolent, non-electoral, participatory entities]]\n** [[Ethnic]]/[[ethno-religious]]/[[racial]]/[[Regionalism (politics)|regional]]/[[Religious organization|religious]] group(s)\n{{TOC right}}\n\n== Azerbaijan ==\n{{Main|Nagorno-Karabakh War}}\n{{Further|List of active separatist movements in Europe}}\n\n;Breakaway state:\n\n{{Flag|Artsakh}}\n* Ethnic group: [[Armenians]]\n** De facto state: [[Republic of Artsakh]]\n** Government-in-exile: [[Azerbaijani Community of Nagorno-Karabakh]]\n\n== Bangladesh ==\n{{flagicon image|}} [[Bangabhumi]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Bengali Hindus]]\n** Region: South-western [[Bangladesh]]\n** Organisation: [[Banga Sena]]\n** Leader: Kalidas Baidya\n** Armed wing: Bir Banga\n\n{{flagicon image|Flag of Parbatya Chattagram Jana Samhati Samiti (PCJSS).png}} [[Chittagong Hill Tracts]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Jumma people]]\n** Political party: [[Parbatya Chattagram Jana Samhati Samiti|Parbotto Chottogram Jonshonghoti Shomiti]]\n* Further information: [[Chittagong Hill Tracts conflict]]\n\n{{flagicon image|}} [[Tripura]]\n** Ethnic group: [[Tripuri people|Tripuri]]\n** Organisation: [[All Tripura Tiger Force]]\n* Leader: [[Ranjit Debbarma]]\n\n{{flagicon image|Flag of Bnei Menashe.svg}} [[Zale'n-gam]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Kuki people]]\n** Region: Eastern borders of [[Bangladesh]] (primarily in parts of the [[Chittagong Hill Tracts]])\n** Organisation: [[Kuki National Organisation]]\n** Leaders: Pu S Haokip, Pu Letlam\n** Armed wing: [[Kuki National Army]]\n\n== China (Mainland China, Hong Kong, Macau) ==\n{{Main|Secession in China}}\n{{See also|Political status of Taiwan|One country, two systems|Ethnic minorities in China}}\n\n*'''The {{flagdeco|PRC}} [[People's Republic of China]] (China or PRC)''' is a state that is [[Foreign relations of China|recognised]] by 177 (out of 192 other) [[Member states of the United Nations|United Nations member states]] (as well as [[State of Palestine|Palestine]], an [[United Nations General Assembly observers|observer]]) as the [[China and the United Nations|sole legitimate government of China]]; the PRC represents China in the [[United Nations]] and is a [[Permanent members of the United Nations Security Council|permanent member of the United Nations Security Council]]. These states (that recognise the PRC's legitimacy) all recognise the [[Mainland|continental]] and island (e.g. [[Hainan]]) territory of \"[[mainland China]]\", which includes certain contentious regions such as [[Tibet]] and [[Xinjiang]], as being part of China (disregarding [[List of territorial disputes|border disputes]]). Mainland China does not include [[Hong Kong]], [[Macau]], and [[Taiwan]].\n**'''The''' {{flagdeco|PRC}} '''PRC's irredentist territorial claim to [[Taiwan]] as \"[[Taiwan Province, People's Republic of China]]\"''' \u2014 Many of the states that recognise the PRC's legitimacy have not clarified whether they specifically recognise China's [[Irredentism|irredentist]] [[Territorial dispute|territorial claim]] to the [[Geography of Taiwan|island of Taiwan]] and its [[List of islands of Taiwan|satellite islands]] (including [[Penghu]], [[Orchid Island]], [[Green Island, Taiwan|Green Island]], etc.), which it has [[History of Taiwan since 1945|never historically administered]]. China claims Taiwan as \"Taiwan Province, People's Republic of China\", but such a [[polity]] has never historically existed. Taiwan was designated a \"[[Provinces of China|province of China]]\" between 1887 and 1895 and a \"[[prefecture]] of [[Fujian|Fujian Province]]\" between 1684 and 1887, in both cases under the [[Qing dynasty]], an [[History of China|historical regime of China]] and the last Chinese [[Empire|imperial]] [[dynasty]]; the Qing dynasty [[Taiwanese indigenous peoples|never exercised absolute control]] over the entire island of Taiwan and its satellite islands.\n*'''The {{flagdeco|HKG}} [[Hong Kong|Hong Kong Special Administrative Region of the People's Republic of China]] (Hong Kong or Hong Kong SAR)''' is a highly autonomous territory whose sovereignty ultimately lies within China (PRC). Hong Kong's autonomy under a so-called [[One country, two systems|One Country Two Systems]] framework officially expires by 2047, at which point it is supposed to be fully integrated into China (PRC).\n*'''The {{flagdeco|MAC}} [[Macau|Macao (Macau) Special Administrative Region of the People's Republic of China]] (Macau/Macao or Macau/Macao SAR)''' is a highly autonomous territory whose sovereignty ultimately lies within China (PRC). Macau's autonomy under a so-called One Country Two Systems framework officially expires by 2049, at which point it is supposed to be fully integrated into China (PRC).\n\n===List of significant secessionist movements in China===\n* {{flagdeco|Taiwan}} [[Taiwan]] is not included in this list because it has never been governed by the [[China|People's Republic of China]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:100%\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"7\" bgcolor=\"#9acdff\" align=\"center\" |'''Significant Secessionist Movements in China'''\n|-\n! width=\"75\" |No.\n! width=\"225\" |Claimed Territory\n! width=\"100\" |Capital City\n! width=\"100\" |Area\n! width=\"100\" |Population\n! width=\"125\" |Ethnic Group\n! width=\"300\" |Primary Independence Movement\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |1 ||'''{{flagdeco|Tibet}} [[Tibet Autonomous Region|Xizang]] ([[Tibet]])'''||[[Lhasa]]|| align=\"center\" |2,500,000 || align=\"center\" |10,000,000 ||[[Tibetan people]]||[[Tibetan independence movement]]\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |2 ||'''{{flagdeco|East Turkestan}} [[Xinjiang]] ([[East Turkestan]])'''||[[\u00dcr\u00fcmqi]]|| align=\"center\" |1,700,000 || align=\"center\" |20,000,000 ||[[Uyghurs|Uyghur people]]||[[East Turkestan independence movement]]\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |3 ||'''[[File:Flag of the Inner Mongolian People's Party.svg|23px|border]] [[Inner Mongolia]]'''||[[Hohhot]]|| align=\"center\" |1,183,000 || align=\"center\" |25,000,000 ||[[Mongols in China|Chinese Mongols]]||[[Inner Mongolian independence movement]]\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |4 ||'''{{flagdeco|Hong Kong}} [[Hong Kong]]'''||[[Hong Kong]]|| align=\"center\" |1,110 || align=\"center\" |7,500,000 ||[[Hongkongers|Hong Kong people]]||[[Hong Kong independence|Hong Kong independence movement]]\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |5 ||'''{{flagdeco|Macau}} [[Macau]]'''||[[Macau]]|| align=\"center\" |115 || align=\"center\" |700,000 ||[[Macau people]]||[[Macau independence|Macau independence movement]]\n|- style=\"background:silver;\"\n| align=\"center\" |'''Total'''||'''{{flagdeco|China}} [[China]]'''||'''[[Beijing]]'''|| align=\"center\" |'''5,384,225'''|| align=\"center\" |'''63,000,000'''||'''[[Chinese people]]'''||'''[[Chinese nationalism]]'''\n|}\n\n=== List of fringe secessionist movements in China ===\n{{More citations needed section|small=y|date=January 2020}}\n* Claimed territories that do not exist are indicated in ''Italics''.\n* Claimed capital cities for non-existent territories are indicated in ''Italics''.\n* Independence movements for non-existent territories are indicated in ''Italics''.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:100%\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"7\" bgcolor=\"#9acdff\" align=\"center\" |'''Fringe Secessionist Movements in China'''\n|-\n! width=\"75\" |No.\n! width=\"225\" |Claimed Territory\n!Capital City\n! width=\"100\" |Area\n! width=\"100\" |Population\n! width=\"125\" |Ethnic Group\n! width=\"300\" |Primary Independence Movement\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |1 ||'''{{flagdeco|Manchukuo}} [[Northeast China|Dongbei]] ([[Manchuria]])'''\n|[[Harbin]] (Halbin)\n| align=\"center\" |787,000 || align=\"center\" | 112,000,000 ||[[Manchu people]]||[[Manchukuo Temporary Government]]\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |2 ||'''[[File:Flag of Yuyencia.png|23px|border]] [[Hebei]], [[Beijing]] and [[Tianjin]]'''\n|[[Harbin]] (Halbin)\n| align=\"center\" |113,000,000 || align=\"center\" | 118,000,000 ||Yuyencian people||[[Yuyencian regionalism]]\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |3 ||'''[[File:Flag of Basuria Independence Movement and the Republic of Basuria.png|23px|border]] [[Sichuan]] (Szechuan)'''\n|[[Chengdu]] (Chengtu)\n| align=\"center\" |485,000 || align=\"center\" |81,000,000 ||[[Sichuanese people]]||Bashu nationalism\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |4 ||'''[[Guangdong]] (Kwangtung)'''\n|[[Gua