y 2020}}\n\n* Ethno-religious group: [[Terms for Syriac Christians#Arameans|Arameans]]\n** Proposed state: [[File:ArameanFlag.png|22px|border]] [[Aram (biblical region)|Aramaean Republic]]\n** Political parties: [[Aramean Democratic Organisation]]\n** Advocacy group: [[World Council of Arameans (Syriacs)]]\n\n== Malaysia ==\n{{Main|Secession in the Malaysia}}\n{{see also | Proposed 2019 amendment to the Constitution of Malaysia | History_of_the_Republic_of_Singapore#Expulsion_from_Malaysia | l2 = Separation of Singapore from Malaysia}}\n\n{{flagdeco|Johor}} [[Johor]]\n*Proposed state: Johor<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.malaysiakini.com/news/344165|title=Bukan TMJ atau PM tentukan Johor keluar Malaysia|date=5 June 2016|publisher=malaysiakini.com|language=Malay}}</ref>\n**Paramilitary organizations: [[Royal Johor Military Force|Askar Timbalan Setia Johor]]\n\n{{flagdeco|Kelantan}} [[Kelantan]]\n*Ethnic group: [[Kelantanese]]\n**Proposed state: Kelantan<ref>http://www.sabahsarawakmerdeka.com/2014/09/kelantan-keluar-malaysia.html</ref>\n\n{{flagdeco|Sarawak}} [[Sarawak]]<ref name=\"ss\">{{cite web |url=http://www.theborneopost.com/2014/08/13/group-draws-up-self-determination-petition-for-sarawak-and-sabah/ |title=Group draws up self determination petition for Sarawak and Sabah |work=[[Borneo Post]] |date=13 August 2014 |accessdate=12 November 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141112084812/http://www.theborneopost.com/2014/08/13/group-draws-up-self-determination-petition-for-sarawak-and-sabah/ |archive-date=12 November 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"ssn\">{{cite web |url=http://www.therakyatpost.com/news/2014/02/16/many-in-sabah-sarawak-dont-want-to-be-part-of-malaysia-claims-analyst/ |title=Many in Sabah, Sarawak don't want to be part of Malaysia, claims analyst |work=[[The Rakyat Post]] |date=16 February 2014 |accessdate=12 November 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304104837/http://www.therakyatpost.com/news/2014/02/16/many-in-