s.com/2019/09/19/world/asia/pakistan-kashmir-independence.html</ref>\n* Advocacy group: [[Kashmiri sovereignty movement]], [[Azad Kashmiri Government]]\n \n[[File:Flag of Balochistan.svg|border|22px]] [[Balochistan (Pakistan)|Balochistan]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Baloch people|Baloch]]\n** Proposed state: [[Balochistan]] [[File:BRA flag.jpg|22px|border]] along with [[Sistan and Baluchestan]] of [[Iran]] and [[Balochistan, Afghanistan|some parts]] of [[Afghanistan]].<ref>{{cite book|title=The Redefined Dimensions of Baloch Nationalist Movement|author=Malik Siraj Akbar|quote=The ultimate goal of BLA is \u201cGreater Balochistan\u201d, a country that will comprise the Baloch areas of Pakistani and Iranian Balochistan provinces and some parts of Afghanistan.|page=29|publisher=Xlibris Corporation|date=30 March 2011}}</ref>\n** Political party: [[Baloch National Movement]], [[Baloch Republican Party]], [[Free Balochistan Movement]] (member of the [[Unrepresented Nations and Peoples Organization]])\n** Militant organisations: [[Baloch Liberation Army]], [[Baloch Liberation Front]], [[Baloch Republican Army]]\n\n[[File:Brahuistan.jpg|20x20px]] [[Brahui people|Brahuistan]] \n* Ethnic group: [[Brahui people|Brahui]]\n** Proposed state: [[File:Brahuistan.jpg|20x20px]] [[Brahuistan]]\n\n{{main|Sindhi nationalism}}\n[[File:Flag of Sindh.svg|22px|border]] [[Sindh]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bansal |first1=Alok |title=Violent Sindhi nationalism raises its head again |url=http://southasiamonitor.org/detail.php?type=n&nid=2992 |website=South Asia Monitor |accessdate=23 November 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151123092427/http://southasiamonitor.org/detail.php?type=n&nid=2992 |archive-date=23 November 2015 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Now Sindhis Demand Independent Nation In Pakistan|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/world-news-now-sindhi-activists-demand-for-independent-nation-in-pakistan/323750|website=Outlook|access-date=15 November 2019|url-s