\"unite\">{{cite news |last1=Bitog |first1=Rubyloida |title=Elders unite Bodong factions |url=http://archive.sunstar.com.ph/baguio/local-news/2013/04/21/elders-unite-bodong-factions-278706 |accessdate=6 October 2017 |work=Sun Star Baguio |date=21 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171006212031/http://archive.sunstar.com.ph/baguio/local-news/2013/04/21/elders-unite-bodong-factions-278706 |archive-date=6 October 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n[[National Capital Region (Philippines)|National Capital Region]]\n* Proposed autonomous area: [[Metro Manila]] Autonomous Region<ref>{{cite news |title=QC mayor Bautista seeks 'independent Metro Manila state' |url=https://www.rappler.com/nation/179009-quezon-city-mayor-herbert-bautista-independent-metro-manila-state |accessdate=31 August 2017 |work=Rappler |date=17 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170831083111/https://www.rappler.com/nation/179009-quezon-city-mayor-herbert-bautista-independent-metro-manila-state |archive-date=31 August 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n[[Federal Republic of Mindanao]]\n*[[Mindanao]], [[Palawan (island)|Palawan]] and [[Sulu Archipelago|Sulu]]\n\n== Russia ==\n{{More citations needed section|small=y|date=January 2020}}\n{{Main|Secession in Russia}}\n{{See also|List of active separatist movements in Europe#Russia|Asian Russia|Indigenous peoples of Siberia}}\n\n===Summary===\nThis table shows only the list of movements. The source of each movement is cited in its own section. The population of each area is provided for information only.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:100%\"\n|-\n!width=75|Number\n!width=250|Land\n!width=125|Capital\n!width=100|Area\n!width=100|Population\n!width=125|Ethnic\n!width=300|Main Political Party\n|-\n| colspan=\"7\" bgcolor=\"#9acdff\" align=\"center\" |'''All of [[Asian Russia]]'''\n|-\n| align=center|1 || '''[[File:Siberian flag.svg|23px|border]] [[Siberian Republic]]''' || '''[[Novosibirsk]]''' || align=center|13,100,000